        protected JInvocation(@Nonnull
                      AbstractJType aConstructorType)
        Invokes a constructor of an object (i.e., creates a new object.)
        Parameters:
        aConstructorType - Type of the object to be created. If this type is an array type, added arguments are treated as array initializer. Thus you can create an expression like new int[]{1,2,3,4,5}.
